Lagos State Police Commissioner Imohimi Edgal has ordered the investigation of an officer, for allegedly torturing a good Samaritan. This is contained in a statement signed by the Copmmand’s spokesman, Chike Oti, a Chief Superintendent of Police (CSP). Oti did not name the officer. Oti said the order followed media report on “Police torture good Samaritan for trying to free extortion victim.” “Following the publication, the CP has directed the Deputy Commissioner of Police in charge of the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department (SCIID), to withdraw the case from court for reinvestigation. “The CP directed the DC, SCIID to constitute an investigative panel and invite the parties involved in the matter, including the police officer that handled the case, for thorough enquiries. “If the officer is found guilty, he will face disciplinary action. “The command frowns on any act of rights abuse against anybody, irrespective of their class or background,” Oti said. He said the outcome of the investigation would be made public. 